59
00:02:30,975 --> 00:02:33,837
So, but before the disability,

60
00:02:33,837 --> 00:02:35,699
how do we see color normally?

61
00:02:35,699 --> 00:02:39,521
So, in our eyes, we have two types of photoreceptor cells.

62
00:02:39,521 --> 00:02:42,283
We have rods and we have cones.

63
00:02:42,283 --> 00:02:44,525
The rods detect low-level light.

64
00:02:44,525 --> 00:02:46,947
So this is your night vision,

65
00:02:46,947 --> 00:02:50,369
like which you don't have very good color

66
00:02:50,369 --> 00:02:51,190
in your night vision.

67
00:02:51,190 --> 00:02:53,251
The rods just pick up basically, I don't know,

68
00:02:53,251 --> 00:02:54,292
black and white.

69
00:02:54,292 --> 00:02:57,014
And so low-level light to kind of help you survive.

70
00:02:57,512 --> 00:03:00,094
And they talk about many animals being colorblind.

71
00:03:00,094 --> 00:03:01,816
They have rods.

72
00:03:01,816 --> 00:03:03,717
They are effective at low-level vision.

73
00:03:03,717 --> 00:03:05,139
They don't need the color.

74
00:03:05,139 --> 00:03:09,002
Yeah, as I said.

75
00:03:09,002 --> 00:03:11,824
Cones are where we get all our color from.

76
00:03:11,824 --> 00:03:14,246
So they detect intense light.

77
00:03:14,246 --> 00:03:16,588
And we have three types of them.

78
00:03:16,588 --> 00:03:19,550
We have our red cones, our blue cones, and our green cones.

79
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:21,932
And all the colors we see are combinations

80
00:03:21,932 --> 00:03:24,435
of these three hues in one way or another.

81
00:03:25,316 --> 00:03:29,341
And if you're lucky enough to have normal color vision,

82
00:03:29,341 --> 00:03:33,766
this is known as trichromacy, so three chromatic.

83
00:03:33,766 --> 00:03:36,609
So there are multiple types of color blindness as well.

84
00:03:36,609 --> 00:03:40,574
So more than just even the three.

85
00:03:40,574 --> 00:03:43,958
So we have deuteranomaly, protanomaly, tritanomaly.

86
00:03:44,969 --> 00:03:46,310
These are known as anomalous trichromacy.

87
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:51,593
This is where there is a defect with the cones in your eyes,

88
00:03:51,593 --> 00:03:53,274
one of the types of cones.

89
00:03:53,274 --> 00:03:54,955
But you still have those cells.

90
00:03:54,955 --> 00:03:58,997
Then there is deuteranopia, which I suffer from,

91
00:03:58,997 --> 00:04:00,518
protanopia, and tritanopia.

92
00:04:00,518 --> 00:04:03,339
These are dichromacy.

93
00:04:03,339 --> 00:04:06,621
One of the types of cones is basically missing.

94
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:12,394
And the different names are depending on which cone is missing.

95
00:04:12,394 --> 00:04:16,857
So deuteranopia is, well, I'll go into some more detail shortly.

96
00:04:16,857 --> 00:04:20,460
I mentioned that this doesn't mean we see in black and white.

97
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:23,202
But there are some people that do.

98
00:04:23,202 --> 00:04:24,683
This is a very rare condition.

99
00:04:24,683 --> 00:04:26,685
It is called achromatopsia.

100
00:04:26,685 --> 00:04:28,866
And it is, of course, monochromatic.

101
00:04:28,866 --> 00:04:31,168
And this only affects roughly one in 30,000 people.

102
00:04:32,363 --> 00:04:33,844
except in one place in the world.

103
00:04:33,844 --> 00:04:36,066
There is an island in Pingelap,

104
00:04:36,066 --> 00:04:38,367
it's in Micronesia in the Pacific,

105
00:04:38,367 --> 00:04:43,431
and around 25% of their population have achromatopsia.

106
00:04:43,431 --> 00:04:46,633
This was because of a natural disaster

107
00:04:46,633 --> 00:04:47,914
that wiped out most of the island,

108
00:04:47,914 --> 00:04:53,958
and in repopulating, one of the survivors had achromatopsia,

109
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:56,539
and then this was passed down

110
00:04:56,539 --> 00:04:59,902
to a large part of the population through the genetics.

111
00:05:02,185 --> 00:05:05,466
I'm going to focus on these three,

112
00:05:05,466 --> 00:05:06,827
because supporting deuteranopia,

113
00:05:06,827 --> 00:05:11,089
protanopia, and tritanopia accommodates

114
00:05:11,089 --> 00:05:14,051
for the anomalous trichromacies above,

115
00:05:14,051 --> 00:05:17,012
because these are the most extreme versions of them.

116
00:05:17,012 --> 00:05:18,633
So, first off, deuteranopia,

117
00:05:18,633 --> 00:05:20,774
which is, of those of you that raised your hands

118
00:05:20,774 --> 00:05:23,776
and said you were colorblind, this is probably you.

119
00:05:23,776 --> 00:05:26,237
This is the most common type of red-green colorblindness.

120
00:05:26,237 --> 00:05:30,379
In effect, of all colorblind men,

121
