159
00:07:21,775 --> 00:07:24,016
to the other types of colorblindness.

160
00:07:24,016 --> 00:07:25,737
This is on chromosome seven,

161
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:26,858
and this is not.

162
00:07:27,962 --> 00:07:29,422
rather than the X and Y.

163
00:07:29,422 --> 00:07:30,903
And this is equal between men and women.

164
00:07:30,903 --> 00:07:35,265
And this focuses on a reduced sensitivity

165
00:07:35,265 --> 00:07:37,265
to blue and yellow light.

166
00:07:37,265 --> 00:07:40,046
And so it's not often heard, there aren't many people,

167
00:07:40,046 --> 00:07:41,807
they don't speak up about the issue,

168
00:07:41,807 --> 00:07:43,928
and so people don't expect these problems.

169
00:07:43,928 --> 00:07:46,809
So blue greens and grays are a problem,

170
00:07:46,809 --> 00:07:48,510
dark purples, they can become black,

171
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:50,591
and oranges with reds.

172
00:07:50,591 --> 00:07:54,512
So where does this come from?

173
00:07:54,512 --> 00:07:56,513
So a little biology lesson.

174
00:07:57,682 --> 00:08:00,504
Men have an X chromosome and a Y chromosome,

175
00:08:00,504 --> 00:08:02,305
women have two X chromosomes.

176
00:08:02,305 --> 00:08:06,668
The advantage of this is that if there is a defect

177
00:08:06,668 --> 00:08:09,450
on an X chromosome for a woman,

178
00:08:09,450 --> 00:08:10,891
if the chromosome is fine on the other one,

179
00:08:10,891 --> 00:08:12,412
she does not suffer from the condition.

180
00:08:12,412 --> 00:08:16,915
There are many conditions that are more prevalent in men

181
00:08:16,915 --> 00:08:19,417
for this very reason, because if I have a problem

182
00:08:19,417 --> 00:08:22,279
on my X chromosome, and I do,

183
00:08:22,279 --> 00:08:24,281
my Y chromosome can't compensate.

184
00:08:24,281 --> 00:08:27,023
It doesn't have the reflective.

185
00:08:27,598 --> 00:08:29,259
chromosomes to back it up.

186
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:31,800
And so colorblindness is mostly hereditary.

187
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:36,523
Deuteranopia and protanopia are a defect on the X chromosome.

188
00:08:36,523 --> 00:08:39,045
And so this is passed down,

189
00:08:39,045 --> 00:08:41,526
and this will be passed down to men.

190
00:08:41,526 --> 00:08:44,728
And it has to come from their mother, in this case,

191
00:08:44,728 --> 00:08:47,450
because a man passes a Y chromosome to their son.

192
00:08:47,450 --> 00:08:51,172
A woman can be a carrier,

193
00:08:51,172 --> 00:08:53,974
and it's then basically a 50-50 chance

194
00:08:53,974 --> 00:08:56,035
does she pass the defective X chromosome to her son.

195
00:08:56,657 --> 00:09:00,721
For a woman to be colorblind of one of these two,

196
00:09:00,721 --> 00:09:02,643
her father must be colorblind

197
00:09:02,643 --> 00:09:05,966
because that X chromosome must come down,

198
00:09:05,966 --> 00:09:08,068
and then it's a 50-50 from her mother.

199
00:09:08,068 --> 00:09:10,611
If her mother is colorblind and her father is colorblind,

200
00:09:10,611 --> 00:09:11,152
she's getting it.

201
00:09:11,152 --> 00:09:11,412
I am sorry.

202
00:09:11,412 --> 00:09:14,555
Tritonopure, of course, is different.

203
00:09:14,555 --> 00:09:17,618
This is defective chromosome seven.

204
00:09:17,618 --> 00:09:19,540
This is not a sexual chromosome.

205
00:09:21,058 --> 00:09:24,459
But also, this one can be triggered by other issues in the brain.

206
00:09:24,459 --> 00:09:26,760
So there can be illnesses and injuries,

207
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:31,082
